## Core Runtime Flows

### Synchronous Document Indexing

```text
POST /api/v1/documents/upload
-> load_uploaded_document()
-> chunk_document()
-> index_document_chunks()
-> embedding_client.embed_texts()
-> redis_store.save_document_chunk()
```

### Async Document Indexing

```text
POST /api/v1/documents/upload/async
-> create_document_index_task()
-> redis_store.save_index_task(pending)
-> RQDocumentIndexQueue.enqueue_document_index_task()
-> worker run_document_index_task()
-> loader/chunker/indexer
-> redis_store.save_index_task(done/failed)
```

### Retrieval

```text
POST /api/v1/documents/search
-> retrieve_document_chunks()
-> optional query_rewriter.rewrite()
-> embedding_client.embed_text()
-> redis_store.search_document_chunks()
-> optional rerank_client.rerank()
```

Redis vector distance is distance, not a "higher is better" score. Smaller distance usually means semantically closer.

### RAG Answering

```text
POST /api/v1/rag/query
-> answer_rag_query()
-> retrieve_document_chunks()
-> to_rag_sources()
-> build_rag_messages()
-> llm_client.chat()
-> RagQueryResponse(answer, sources)
```

If no sources are retrieved, the system returns a no-context answer and does not call the LLM.

### Agent Run

```text
POST /api/v1/agent/run
-> run_agent_workflow()
-> load_memory
-> understand_intent
-> decide_retrieval
-> call_tools or skip_tools
-> generate_answer
-> save_trace
-> AgentRunResponse(answer, intent, steps, sources, checkpoint)
```

Intent routing is mostly deterministic:

- arithmetic -> `calculator`
- todo -> `create_todo`
- weekly report -> `draft_weekly_report`
- file summary -> `summarize_file`
- explicit memory update -> `memory_profile`
- job application data question -> `query_database`
- knowledge question -> RAG/search docs
- general chat -> LLM, optionally with bounded tool calls

### Job-Application HITL Flow

```text
POST /api/v1/agent/job-application/review
-> resume_analyst
-> jd_matcher
-> human_review interrupt

POST /api/v1/agent/job-application/resume
-> Command(resume=decision)
-> material_writer
-> JobApplicationReviewResponse(completed)
```

This is a specific human-in-the-loop workflow for job-application material generation. It is not the same as a production-grade generic resume API for `/agent/run`.

